commit.message:
Support custom sort in serialization methods (#379)

* Support custom sort in serialization methods

* Actually pass sort_key to to_str

* Simplify sorting, sort on way in and out

Changes in registry.resolve were needed because we want to make sure to not convert any intermediate state to a Config object – otherwise, this would result in the keys getting sorted constantly, including keys of subsections

* Increment version

* Preserve section order in copy and merge

* Also preserve section order from existing config

* Preserve section order when config is filled

commit.message: Add test for filling with extra values
Add test for coerced values: resolved vs. filled

Make resolved config a dict

No point in making it a Config object because it's not really a valid config – it contains arbitrary Python objects, can't be serialized or interpolated as a config, etc.
Fix reporting of whether config is interpolated

Support optional variable interpolation and fix config resolution (#377)

* Support optional variable interpolation and fix config resolution

* Fix handling of non-serializable values

* Assume is_interpolated=True by default

Prevents unnecessary to_str/from_str roundtrips when config is resolved from Config produced by registry.fill etc.

* Add xfailing test for feature we might want to support

* Only keep original variable if new value isn't variable

* Increment version

* Remove test

* Make Config.merge regular method

Co-authored-by: Matthew Honnibal <honnibal+gh@gmail.com>
